👉 Problem: (Leetcode 74, Binary Search in 2D Matrix)

✅ Key Idea
The given matrix is “flattened sorted”:

Each row is sorted.
First element of a row > last element of the previous row.

So if you read the matrix row by row, it’s equivalent to a 1D sorted array of length m * n.
That means we can apply binary search directly on this “virtual” 1D array.

✨ Flashcard
"Flatten 2D → pretend it’s 1D → binary search with index mapping (row = mid // n, col = mid % n)."

⚡ Full Approach

Matrix size:
Rows = m
Cols = n
Total elements = m * n.

Binary Search:
Search range: left = 0, right = m * n - 1.

Midpoint: mid = (left + right) // 2.

Index Mapping:
Convert 1D mid index to 2D (row, col) using:
row = mid // n
col = mid % n

Check:

If matrix[row][col] == target → return True.
If matrix[row][col] < target → search right half.
Else → search left half.
If loop ends, return False.

⏱️ Complexity

Time: O(log(m * n)) (binary search on all elements).
Space: O(1) (only a few variables).

