👉 Problem: Build Binary Tree from Preorder and Inorder (Leetcode 105)

✅ Key Idea

Preorder gives the root first.
Inorder tells us how to split the tree into left and right subtrees.
Recursively apply the same idea to build subtrees.

✨ Flashcard
"Preorder → pick root. Inorder → split left/right. Recurse."

⚡ Full Approach

Base Case:

If preorder or inorder is empty → return None.

Pick Root:

root_val = preorder[0] → first element in preorder is the root.
Create root = TreeNode(root_val).

Find Root Index in Inorder:
mid = inorder.index(root_val)

Everything before mid → left subtree.
Everything after mid → right subtree.
Build Subtrees Recursively:

Left: preorder[1:mid+1], inorder[:mid]
Right: preorder[mid+1:], inorder[mid+1:]

Return Root:

root now has left and right children attached.

⏱️ Complexity

Time: O(n²) → index() search at each recursive call.
Space: O(n) → recursion stack and new slices.

✅ Notes

Using a hashmap to store inorder indices can reduce time to O(n).
Works only if all node values are unique.
This approach reconstructs the original tree exactly.

