👉 Problem: Last Stone Weight (LeetCode 1046)

✅ Key Idea

We always smash the two heaviest stones together.
After each smash:
If equal → both destroyed
If not equal → remaining stone = y - x (heavier minus lighter)
To efficiently find the two largest stones each turn → use a max-heap.

✨ Flashcard
"Use a max-heap to always get the two largest stones. Smash them. Push the result if non-zero."

⚡ Full Approach

Convert all stones to a max-heap.
